parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the PPS sensor can cause the airbag system to malfunction, leading to potential injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The "Service Air Bag" light remains on
the passenger airbag light is off
the airbag warning indicator fails to illuminate when the seat is occupied
and the sensor sometimes works and sometimes doesn't.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear differential can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Grinding noise
clunking
whining
binding
or leaking of the rear differential
which can lead to loss of control
accidents
or vehicle stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch master cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or does not start
the ignition switch shuts off during operation
the ignition switch does not engage properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause the airbags to not deploy in the event of an accident, which can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag light is illuminated
the airbag system does not function properly
the airbag does not deploy in the event of an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the airbag warning light to flash, indicating a potential safety risk, and may also prevent the airbags from deploying in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Airbag warning light flashes
airbag warning light remains illuminated
faulty passenger seat module
faulty seat belt tensioner
and faulty airbag passenger sensor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Ignition switch fails to turn
ignition switch locks up
key becomes stuck in the ignition
and vehicle fails to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to suddenly brake hard, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Vehicle suddenly brakes hard
jolts
and two engine indicator lights go on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the blower motor resistor can cause a fire hazard, as it can melt and short circuit.
symptoms: Blower motor resistor shorts out and melts
and smoke comes out from under the dash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag deployment can cause serious injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in the event of an accident.
